title: Error code list which need to be updated to new format

labels.name: E-easy
labels.description: Call for participation: Experience needed to fix: Easy / not much (good first issue)

labels.name: A-diagnostics
labels.description: Area: Messages for errors, warnings, and lints

labels.name: metabug
labels.description: Issues about issues themselves ("bugs about bugs")

labels.name: E-mentor
labels.description: Call for participation: This issue has a mentor. Use RustcContributor::new on Zulip for discussion.

labels.name: C-tracking-issue
labels.description: Category: A tracking issue for an RFC or an unstable feature.

body:
If you want to work on one (or more) of the issues, just comment on it to say you're taking it!

You can read @jonathandturner's [post about how to make the fixes](http://www.jonathanturner.org/2016/08/helping-out-with-rust-errors.html).  If you have any questions, ask us here or on #rust-internals on irc.mozilla.org.

Also, if you finish an issue and it has a "Bonus" part that you're not able to complete, just go ahead and close the issue and open a new issue for just the Bonus part.  That way, someone else can jump in and work on the bonus part. You can cc me on the new issue and we can add it to the list above.
